        "committer": {
          "name": "Isaac Huang",
          "email": "he.huang@intel.com",
          "date": "2015-03-25 17:24:57.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-6195 osd-zfs: dmu_tx_hold_zap() called with wrong keys",
        "message": "LU-6195 osd-zfs: dmu_tx_hold_zap() called with wrong keys\n\nThe osd_declare_object_destroy() calls dmu_tx_hold_zap() with buf\nthat holds string representation of the FID for the inode accounting\nZAPs. This is wrong as the keys for these ZAPs are not the FID. Since\nthe code will be obsoleted by ZFS object accounting feature, just\nreplace buf with NULL, and zap_count_write() will use worst-case\nestimate. Same for osd_declare_object_create().\n\nChange-Id: If266aad595a5556c5e3ac4a47930c909d7cc86f1\nSigned-off-by: Isaac Huang <he.huang@intel.com>\nTest-Parameters: mdtfilesystemtype=zfs mdsfilesystemtype=zfs ostfilesystemtype=zfs\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
